				<p><p>If you're using four traditional wheels (all have friction) you should power all of them (skid steer). Otherwise your robot has to drag the unpowered wheels when you turn. You can also over come this problem by using two unpowered frictionless wheels instead giving you differential steering.</p>
</p><br>
