				<p><p>The best option would be to use two wheels. Then one motor for each wheel in total two. Then, you can use roller coaster at the front. You do not need to provide power to that. Just provide power to back two wheels. By varying the speed of two back wheels (differential drive) you can move straight and turn as well.</p>
